children.text: The wall insulation batts have not been properly fitted to the timber lintels.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 3999 Thermal Insulation of Dwellings - Bulk Insulation - Installation Requirements, states in section 5.4.2 that

‘Trimming or a reduction in insulation thickness may be required where a structural member such as a timber lintel or services such as plumbing, cables, ducts, flues and the like obstruct the insulation layer’
‘The total wall area shall be insulated with the specified R-value (see Figure 5.4.3.1.3)’ .
The wall insulation batts must be installed over the lintels to ensure thermal performance prior to the plaster installation.
